Matthews does it again Devante Matthews made a one-handed grab against Morristown West on Thursday. WBIR 10:46 p.m. EDT October 22, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Sevier County's Devante Matthews has already made ESPN's SportsCenter "Top 10" once this season. Thursday night against Morristown West, Matthews made another "Top 10" worthy play. 
In the second half, quarterback Deuce Wallace tossed up a bomb and Matthews laid out for the one-handed grab. The Smoky Bears would cap the drive with a touchdown from Matthews. Sevier County went on to beat Morristown West and secure the region title, 35-21. 
Matthews previously made SportsCenter's "Top 10" with a one-handed grab against Cocke County. Devante Matthews made SportsCenter with this one-handed grab vs. Cocke County. WBIR Read or Share this story: http://on.wbir.com/1S03Pz4 TOP VIDEOS
